oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: A cattle and sheep pasture on the farm of Mr. S.C. Dunbar near Dotsonville in Montgomery County, Tennessee.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: The loblolly pine plantation in the background was planted by the C.C.C. in 1935. Sheep and cattle have used it as an "outdoor barn" in winter and for shade in the summer since 1941. The growth of the trees appear to have been slowed by this use.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Administrative agencies; Farms; Forests; Livestock; Pines
